
Unit 16 


16.1 Write a sentence with just for each picture.

1 They've just arrived.
2 He's just got up.
3 they've just bougth a car.
4 the race's just started.

16.2 Complete the sentences. Use already + present perfect.

1 what time's paul arrvining? He's already arrived.
2 do your friends wanna see the film?  no, they've already seen it.
3 don't forget to phone tom. I've already phoned him.
4 when is mark going away? he's already gone away.
5 do you wanna read the  newspaper? I've already readed it.
6 when does sarah start her new jow? she's already started it.

16.3 Write a sentence with just (They've ju s t... / She's ju s t... etc.) or a negative sentence with yet
(They haven't... yet / She hasn't... yet etc.).

1 she hasn't gone out yet.
2 the bus has just gone.
2 the train hasn't left yet. 
4 he's hasnt opned it yet.
5 they've finished their dinner.
6 it's just stoped raining.

16.4 Write questions with yet.

1 Your friend has a new job. Perhaps she has started it. You ask her:
Have you started your new job yet?

2 Your friend has some new neighbours. Perhaps he has met them. You ask him:
have you met your neighbours yet?

3 Your friend has to pay her electricity bill. Perhaps she has paid it. You ask her:
have you paid your the electricity bill yet?

4 Tom was trying to sell his car. Perhaps he has sold it. You ask a friend about Tom:
he sold his car yet?